  "description": "Agon is one of Roger Caillois\u0026rsquo;s four fundamental categories of play: play structured around competition. In agonistic play, the outcome depends on the participants\u0026rsquo; skill, strategy, effort, or endurance. Chess, wrestling, debate, track and field, and most sports are agonistic. The defining feature is that the players themselves are the primary source of uncertainty — the game\u0026rsquo;s interest comes from not knowing who will prove more capable under the conditions the game establishes.\n",
